You can pack the wsdl2java generated classes as a jar file and add it in class path and then intiate the `@WebMethod` class for calling the service. 

Refer to the section &quot;Coding the Client&quot; in the documentation [here][1]  


I assume you could do something like this.

```        
        UserServiceImplService serviceImpl = new UserServiceImplService();

        UserService service = serviceImpl.getUserServiceImplPort();

        UserRequest userRequest = new UserRequest();
        userRequest.setFirstName(&quot;Tom&quot;);
        userRequest.setLastName(&quot;Jerry&quot;);

        User user = service.addUser(userRequest);
```

here is an example https://github.com/nkumarclm/jax-ws-example jaxws for your reference.


Also, another way is to use [jaxws-maven-plugin][2] in your `pom.xml` which way you could keep the wsdl copy locally and generate all the required artifacts.

            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.codehaus.mojo&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;jaxws-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;executions&gt;
                    &lt;execution&gt;
                        &lt;id&gt;web-services&lt;/id&gt;
                        &lt;goals&gt;
                            &lt;goal&gt;wsimport&lt;/goal&gt;
                        &lt;/goals&gt;
                        &lt;configuration&gt;
                            &lt;wsdlDirectory&gt;${basedir}/src/main/resources/wsdl/&lt;/wsdlDirectory&gt; //location of your wsdl folder
                            &lt;wsdlFiles&gt;
                                &lt;wsdlFile&gt;user.wsdl&lt;/wsdlFile&gt; //wsdl file name
                            &lt;/wsdlFiles&gt;
                            &lt;sourceDestDir&gt;${basedir}/src/generated/java&lt;/sourceDestDir&gt;
                            &lt;verbose&gt;true&lt;/verbose&gt;
                        &lt;/configuration&gt;
                    &lt;/execution&gt;
                &lt;/executions&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;


then you could simply autowire the `@WebMethod` class and invoke `addUser` method.


